---
id: org.dxos.ui-editor.outliner
name: Outliner
version: 0.1.0
---

The outliner is a CodeMirror extension (`outliner()`) that turns a plain markdown
task/bullet list into a structured, hierarchical outline editor. The document is
always valid markdown — nesting is leading-whitespace indentation, items are
`- [ ] ` tasks or `- ` bullets — so the same text round-trips through any markdown
tool and syncs as ordinary text.

It is built **on top of `../blocks`**, which owns whole-block selection, the gutter
drag grip, the selection highlight, and the clipboard. The outliner contributes only
what is hierarchy/markdown-specific: tree parsing, edit constraints, structural
commands, the drag re-indent rule, and the item menu. See `DESIGN.md` for the
rebuild rationale and the drag-reindent derivation; this spec is the normative
behavior.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term     | URI                       |
| -------- | ------------------------- |
| `module` | `org.dxos.mdl.module@1.0` |
| `feat`   | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`   |
| `test`   | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`   |

## Modules

`outliner()` composes these modules (source files under `src/extensions/structure/outliner/`);
selection, drag, highlight, and clipboard come from `../blocks`.

```mdl
module tree
  desc: |
    Parses the markdown list into an item Tree, recomputed as a facet on doc change. Items expose
    lineRange (own lines), contentRange (text after the marker), level, type, and child/sibling links.
  api:
    Item: interface                         # { type: 'task'|'bullet'; level; lineRange; contentRange; children; ... }.
    Tree: interface                         # find(pos) | traverse(item?, cb) | prev/next | siblings | lastDescendant.
    treeFacet: Facet<Tree>                  # the current parse, read by every other module.
    getRange: (tree, item) => [from, to]    # the item's whole subtree span (item + descendants).
    outlinerTree: () => Extension           # installs the parser + facet.
```

```mdl
module editor
  desc: |
    A transactionFilter constraining edits to a valid outline: snaps the caret out of the marker into
    the content range, allows whole-line deletes, and guards marker/continuation edits. Seeds an empty
    document with a first item.
  api:
    editor: () => Extension
```

```mdl
module commands
  desc: |
    Keymap + exported structural commands. Indent/outdent and move operate on the whole subtree;
    delete/toggle operate on the action scope (see feat F-6).
  api:
    indentItemMore / indentItemLess: Command   # Tab / Shift-Tab — re-indent the caret item + descendants.
    moveItemUp / moveItemDown: Command         # swap the item (with its subtree) past a sibling.
    deleteItem: Command                        # delete the action scope's subtree(s); clears selection.
    toggleTask: Command                        # toggle the action scope between task and bullet.
    getActionScope: (state) => Item[]          # the block selection (subtrees), else the caret item.
    commands: () => Extension                  # the outliner keymap.
```

```mdl
module dnd
  desc: |
    Adapts `../blocks` drag/selection to the outline: per-item grips, subtree extent, subtree move with
    re-indent, and the drop-level rule. Also the selection commands over blockSelectionField.
  api:
    getBlocks: (state) => Block[]              # per-item own-lines (non-overlapping) for grips/ordering.
    getExtent: (state, block) => Block         # the block's whole subtree (selection/collapse/preview).
    moveBlocks: (view, sources, dropIndex, indent?) => void   # subtree move + re-indent to indent.
    replaceBlocks: (view, indices, text|null) => void         # clipboard cut/paste over item lines.
    getDropIndent: (view, sources, dropIndex, pointerY) => { indent, offset } | null  # feat F-5 rule.
    selectAllItems / selectNoneItems / selectUp / selectDown: Command  # over blockSelectionField.
    outlinerDnd: () => Extension
```

```mdl
module menu
  desc: |
    A floating per-item trigger (⋮) pinned in the right margin, hidden while dragging. Activating it
    opens the host popover; its actions run over the action scope (feat F-6).
  api:
    menu: (options?) => Extension
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Document model

  req F-1.1:
    when: text is a markdown list of `- [ ] ` tasks and `- ` bullets, nested by 2-space indentation
    then: it parses to a Tree of items, each with a level, type, own line range, and subtree

  req F-1.2:
    when: the document changes
    then: the Tree is recomputed and exposed via treeFacet; the document stays valid markdown text

  req F-1.3:
    when: the document is empty
    then: a first item (`- [ ] `) is seeded and the caret placed in its content
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Editing constraints

  req F-2.1:
    when: the caret is moved into an item's marker (before its content start)
    then: it snaps to a valid position — content start when moving down/into, content end when moving
          up, the previous line end when moving left across the marker

  req F-2.2:
    when: a whole item line is deleted
    then: the edit is allowed; marker-internal edits that would break the item are constrained

  req F-2.3:
    when: task-marker atomicity is required (backspace removing a whole marker, continuation indent)
    then: it is enforced by the markdown keymap that shapes the change, not by raw edits
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Selection (single model, subtree unit)

  req F-3.1:
    when: an item is selected via grip click / shift-click / keyboard
    then: the sole selection state is blockSelectionField (anchors); there is no second model

  req F-3.2:
    when: an item is selected or dragged
    then: its visual/operational extent is its whole subtree (getExtent = getRange), so a parent
          covers its descendants

  req F-3.3:
    when: the caret sits in an item and nothing is selected
    then: a subtle current-item border marks that item's subtree, distinct from the selection accent
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Structural commands

  req F-4.1:
    when: Tab / Shift-Tab is pressed on an item
    then: the item AND all its descendants re-indent together (the subtree moves with its parent); Tab
          is a no-op with no shallower-or-equal previous item to nest under

  req F-4.2:
    when: an item is moved up/down
    then: it swaps with the adjacent sibling as whole subtrees

  req F-4.3:
    when: toggleTask runs
    then: every item in the action scope flips uniformly between task and bullet, preserving indent
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Drag and drop re-indent

  req F-5.1:
    when: an item is dragged
    then: its whole subtree lifts (collapsed out) and a floating preview follows the pointer; the
          static grip is hidden and the preview carries its own grip; the menu is hidden

  req F-5.2:
    when: the pointer hovers a drop slot (before target T, with A the item above the slot)
    then: the target level defaults to the dragged item's own level, clamped to
          [sibling-of-T, child-of-A] — it stays in its branch (i)

  req F-5.3:
    when: the slot is a branch boundary (T shallower than the default) AND the pointer is over T's row
    then: the level drops to a sibling of T — it outdents to leave the branch (ii)

  req F-5.4:
    when: the target level differs from the source level
    then: the preview shifts horizontally to preview it, and on drop the subtree re-roots to exactly
          that level (preview and result agree)
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Menu / action scope

  req F-6.1:
    when: a menu command runs with a block selection
    then: it acts over every selected item's whole subtree (the action scope)

  req F-6.2:
    when: a menu command runs with no selection
    then: it acts over the caret item's subtree

  req F-6.3:
    when: delete runs
    then: each scope subtree (with its trailing separator) is removed, overlapping ranges merged, and
          the selection cleared — generalizing to any scope-based command
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-indent-subtree
  given: |
    - [ ] A
      - [ ] B
    - [ ] C
      - [ ] D
  when: Tab on "C"
  then: |
    - [ ] A
      - [ ] B
      - [ ] C
        - [ ] D
  tags: [F-4.1]
```

```mdl
test T-drop-stays-in-branch
  given: |
    - A
      - B
      - C
    - D
  when: B is dragged into the slot before D with the pointer above D's row
  then: |
    - A
      - C
      - B
    - D
  tags: [F-5.2]
```

```mdl
test T-drop-outdents-over-target
  given: |
    - A
      - B
      - C
    - D
  when: B is dragged into the slot before D with the pointer over D's row
  then: |
    - A
      - C
    - B
    - D
  tags: [F-5.3]
```

```mdl
test T-delete-subtree
  given: |
    - [ ] 1
    - [ ] 2
      - [ ] 2.1
      - [ ] 2.2
    - [ ] 3
  when: deleteItem with "2" selected (or the caret in it)
  then: |
    - [ ] 1
    - [ ] 3
  tags: [F-6.1, F-6.3]
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

```mdl
ext module
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.module@1.0
  desc: |
    A source module of the outliner extension (a file under src/extensions/structure/outliner/). The
    file path is inferred from the block name (`commands` -> `commands.ts`). Members are the module's
    public exports.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    api: ApiMap         # public exports (name: TypeExpr # comment)
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```
